President Jacob Zuma has appointed a new SABC board and has put corporate management heavyweight, Bongumusa Makhathini, at its helm. In a statement on Tuesday, the Presidency announced the new members of the embattled broadcaster's board. Makhathini would serve as its chairperson and ANC member, Febe Potgieter-Gqubule, as his deputy. The full list of board members are: Febe Potgieter-Gqubule Krish Naidoo Khanyisile Kweyama John Matisonn Mathatha Tsedu Rachel Kalidass Michael Markovitz Bongumusa Makhathini Victor Rambau Dinkwanyane Mohuba Jack Phalane 